{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.11",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 11 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:1",
      "text": "A deceitful balance is an abomination before the Lord: and a just weight is his will.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:2",
      "text": "Where pride is, there also shall be reproach: but where humility is, there also is wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:3",
      "text": "The simplicity of the just shall guide them: and the deceitfulness of the wicked shall destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:4",
      "text": "Riches shall not profit in the day of revenge: but justice shall deliver from death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:5",
      "text": "The justice of the upright shall make his way prosperous: and the wicked man shall fall by his own wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:6",
      "text": "The justice of the righteous shall deliver them: and the unjust shall be caught in their own snares.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:7",
      "text": "When the wicked man is dead, there shall be no hope any more: and the expectation of the solicitous shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:8",
      "text": "The just is delivered out of distress: and the wicked shall be given up for him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:9",
      "text": "The dissembler with his mouth deceiveth his friend: but the just shall be delivered by knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:10",
      "text": "When it goeth well with the just, the city shall rejoice: and when the wicked perish, there shall be praise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:11",
      "text": "By the blessing of the just the city shall be exalted: and by the mouth of the wicked it shall be overthrown.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:12",
      "text": "He that despiseth his friend, is mean of heart: but the wise man will hold his peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:13",
      "text": "He that walketh deceitfully, revealeth secrets: but he that is faithful, concealeth the thing committed to him by his friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:14",
      "text": "Where there is no governor, the people shall fall: but there is safety where there is much counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:15",
      "text": "He shall be afflicted with evil, that is surety for a stranger: but he that is aware of snares, shall be secure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:16",
      "text": "A gracious woman shall find glory: and the strong shall have riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:17",
      "text": "A merciful man doth good to his own soul: but he that is cruel casteth off even his own kindred.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:18",
      "text": "The wicked maketh an unsteady work: but to him that soweth justice, there is a faithful reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:19",
      "text": "Clemency prepareth life: and the pursuing of evil things, death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:20",
      "text": "A perverse heart is abominable to the Lord: and his will is in them that walk sincerely.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:21",
      "text": "Hand in hand the evil man shall not be innocent: but the seed of the just shall be saved.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:22",
      "text": "A golden ring in a swine's snout, a woman fair and foolish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:23",
      "text": "The desire of the just is all good, the expectation of the wicked is indignation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:24",
      "text": "Some distribute their own goods, and grow richer: others take away what is not their own, and are always in want.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:25",
      "text": "The soul that blesseth, shall be made fat: and he that inebriateth, shall be inebriated also himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:26",
      "text": "He that hideth up corn, shall be cursed among the people: but a blessing upon the head of them that sell.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:27",
      "text": "Well doth he rise early who seeketh good things; but he that seeketh after evil things, shall be oppressed by them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:28",
      "text": "He that trusteth in his riches shall fall: but the just shall spring up as a green leaf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.29",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:29",
      "text": "He that troubleth his own house, shall inherit the winds: and the fool shall serve the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.30",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:30",
      "text": "The fruit of the just man is a tree of life: and he that gaineth souls is wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.11.31",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:31",
      "text": "If the just man receive in the earth, how much more the wicked and the sinner.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
